## What happened

Apple fully removed DSA support from its Security framework. .NET on macOS delegates to that native API, so when .NET 11 adopted the updated macOS SDK, `DSA.Create()` began throwing **`PlatformNotSupportedException`** on macOS. Linux (OpenSSL) and Windows (CNG) still support DSA, which is why only macOS breaks.

## How to fix it

**Option A — Migrate away from DSA (recommended)**
DSA is a legacy algorithm. If you control both signing and verification, switch to **ECDSA** or **Ed25519**. These are supported on all three platforms.

**Option B — Use BouncyCastle for legacy verification**
If you *must* verify existing DSA signatures you can't re-sign:

```bash
dotnet add package BouncyCastle.Cryptography
```

Then replace the platform DSA call with BouncyCastle's managed implementation:

```csharp
using Org.BouncyCastle.Crypto.Parameters;
using Org.BouncyCastle.Crypto.Signers;
using Org.BouncyCastle.Security;

bool VerifyDsaSignature(byte[] publicKeyBytes, byte[] message, byte[] signature)
{
    var keyParam = (DsaPublicKeyParameters)PublicKeyFactory.CreateKey(publicKeyBytes);
    var signer = new DsaSigner();
    signer.Init(forSigning: false, keyParam);

    // Hash the message (DSA operates on a hash)
    var digest = DigestUtilities.GetDigest("SHA-256");
    digest.BlockUpdate(message, 0, message.Length);
    var hash = new byte[digest.GetDigestSize()];
    digest.DoFinal(hash, 0);

    // Decode the DER signature into (r, s)
    var seq = (Org.BouncyCastle.Asn1.Asn1Sequence)
        Org.BouncyCastle.Asn1.Asn1Object.FromByteArray(signature);
    var r = ((Org.BouncyCastle.Asn1.DerInteger)seq[0]).Value;
    var s = ((Org.BouncyCastle.Asn1.DerInteger)seq[1]).Value;

    return signer.VerifySignature(hash, r, s);
}
```

This is a pure managed implementation — no native DSA dependency, works on all platforms.

**Option C — Bundle OpenSSL on macOS**
Set `DOTNET_SYSTEM_SECURITY_CRYPTOGRAPHY_USEOPENSSL=1` (if supported in your runtime version) or P/Invoke into a Homebrew-installed OpenSSL. This is fragile and not recommended for distribution.

**TL;DR:** Apple killed native DSA → .NET 11 can't use it on macOS. Switch to ECDSA, or use BouncyCastle for legacy signature verification.
